item.title: [317]StabbingScape V1.5[317] (source)
item.dc:creator: @CAPT_AMERIKA AMERIKA
item.description:
@CAPT_AMERIKA wrote:

jmood128:

good job but maybe on 2.0 or what ever you can work on cleaning its hugh client.java and taking out the crap

client size doesn’t really matter. What matter’s is how much is called and how large each of them are. It’s all about what you plug into the process booleans, and how large each void or whatever is called on is. If it’s 1 line, its pretty quick on loading the result, while if the void or boolean is a 1000 lines, it will cause a bit of lag, because it has more to process (not in all cases)
